9 years ago, a day like today I went on Craigslist, found an E36 with a blown engine, and I bought it for $600 because… why not. I had raced previously, I had tinkered with cars.. yet I had not gotten deeply involved in the industry.

9 years ago my life changed. I stopped being a touring musician and started pursuing the music business in the back end. Yet I failed miserably at something, I stopped having a way to decompress. 
The birth of this car began on that premise, on our way to find myself again and to find some form of decompression that would release on the pressures of life. I didn’t know that racing would become my life and that I would build multiple businesses around it. 
-
I owe this E36 much of my happiness as well as ventures, friends, and goals that I have achieved. Thank you SirHampton, happy 9th bday with me my son. You’re amazing and have made me a better man. 
-
#feels #e36

Well.. yesterday got lit! The boys and I took the old wide body out and installed the new @bigduckclub V5 kit. In a lapse of 9 hours we removed the old one, trimmed, sanded and installed the new one. Installed the new front lip to the bumper. Got a new hood and make the “RJ Specific” air holes. Aligned the new hood and rear trunk to the new RQP. Fastened everything and went for a loaded it back up in the trailer with the car running and nothing rubbing. All while @eduardo.delgado recording everything and @johnnythedon_ modding his E36 FLCA for more angle; and he welded them himself! 
-
I needed yesterday a lot. I love to work but I needed a break. Thank you boys, your time here meant more than you know. 
-

Story time: 

Have you ever seen the movie City Of God? ..yep that one… The crazy Brazilian Favela one with all the Drug Lords slanging dope and all the kids getting trained and shooting guns. Yeah… thaaaaat one.

Well today I had the pleasure to go to one of the most dangerous Favelas in Rio De Janeiro, and it’s all and nothing like you may think it is. 

Before I tell this story you may be asking how the heck did you ge to go there? Isn’t that gang territory? Won’t even cops go in there? Won’t you get killed because you aren’t from the Favela? And the simple answer is yes…. Unless you get invited and get permission to go in it from the Favela Boss himself. 

The way of how I got invited permitted to go inside is the story, however it’s a long story. I don’t want to write a whole book here but If you’re interested in me writing it / making a video let me know in the comments below and I’ll type it up. 

I truly experienced a day that money can not buy. And more than that, I got to meet ruthless individuals that are …human, have deep feelings, are extremely talented, and live an insanely dangerous lifestyle simply because of lack of resources.
-
#favela #stories #onceinalifetime

A picture is worth a thousand words, and this picture perfectly depicts what drifting is. 
-
Before i officially stuck to Drifting I raced a few different styles: wheel to wheel racing, Time Attack and short course Rally. They all were fun as a driver but some of their communities are toxic as hell. The first time i went to a drifting even I saw something different, I saw drivers laughing with each other, and crews embracing the hard times by helping each other out. The community was different, the mood was lighter, the people were welcoming, and that is what sold me to drifting. 

Now having been in the sport for 10 years i feel like I can go for 30 more simply because of the culture.  Simply because we are there for each other and we embrace each other in the good and bad times. 

Thank you to all my drifting friends for being you. For yours 95% great times and 5% bad ones that have made me grow regardless. I love you all.. and I hope to keep on growing with you for a long time. 

👏⚡️ with @ryanhasinsta 

-RJC12
